-- Citigroup Technical Analysts End Trade Advice to Bet on Euro Appreciation
-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 2010-10-26T11:34:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/citigroup-technical-analysts-end-trade-advice-to-bet-on-euro-appreciation.html
Citigroup Inc. technical analysts
ended trade recommendations to bet the euro will appreciate
against the Swiss franc, U.K. pound and U.S. dollar, citing
“price action in the past 48 hours.”  “We are closing out all of our long euro positions,”
analysts  Tom Fitzpatrick ,  Shyam Devani  and Alex Good said today
in an e-mailed note.  The euro fell 0.3 percent to $1.3928 as of 12:30 p.m. in
London today.  In technical analysis, investors and analysts study charts
of trading patterns and prices to predict changes in a security,
commodity, currency or index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Dobson in London at 
